  "changes": {
    "body": {
      "from": "## Summary\n\nTakes `apps/desktop` from \"quick wins applied\" to release-ready state. Plan: `thoughts/shared/plans/2026-04-23-desktop-pre-release-batch.md`.\n\n**What landed (Phases B–F):**\n- `feat(desktop)`: replace ad-hoc `parseRuntimeEnv` with `@t3-oss/env-core` layer (main + renderer); drop stale `sparklePublicKey`; bake `SENTRY_DSN` into the main bundle via Vite `define` with Sentry-recommended custom-token pattern (`__SENTRY_DSN__`).\n- `feat(desktop)`: Sentry source-map upload script (`pnpm sourcemaps:upload`) covering `.vite/build` + `.vite/renderer/main_window` with `--url-prefix app:///` aligned to `rewriteFramesIntegration`.\n- `ci(desktop)`: enable + harden `desktop-release.yml` — tag trigger `@lightfast/desktop@*`, `cancel-in-progress`, arm64+x64 matrix, codesign + notarize + `actions/attest-build-provenance`, auto-generated release notes from prev tag. Workflow stays inert until a tag is pushed.\n- `ci(desktop)`: new `desktop-ci.yml` — native `paths:` filter on desktop-touching paths, typecheck + unsigned package on `macos-14`.\n- `chore(desktop)`: contributor ergonomics — `.env.example`, `clean` script, `dev:desktop-stack` → `dev:desktop-api` rename, `@lightfast/desktop` added to changesets `ignore`.\n- `feat(desktop)`: wire `dotenv-cli` + `with-env` so `pnpm dev:desktop` loads `.vercel/.env.development.local` into the main process (mirrors `apps/app`).\n\n**Verified in this session:**\n- `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop typecheck` + `pnpm check` (biome/ultracite) green.\n- Bundle baking: `SENTRY_DSN='https://fake@sentry.io/12345' pnpm package` inlines the DSN into `.vite/build`; unset DSN leaves zero `__SENTRY_DSN__` tokens.\n- Missing `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` produces a readable t3-env banner naming the variable.\n- Sourcemap-upload script (mocked `sentry-cli`): 4 calls in order — `releases new`, two `upload-sourcemaps` with `--url-prefix app:///`, `releases finalize`.\n- Desktop CI `paths:` filter: 12/12 cases correct (desktop/packages-* trigger; www/app/platform/other-workflows skip).\n- `desktop-release.yml` structural invariants: tag trigger, concurrency, perms (`id-token`/`attestations: write`), matrix, env surfaces, sourcemap + attestation steps, prev-tag notes.\n- Interactive end-to-end: Clerk sign-in → loopback callback → `GET /api/trpc/account.get 200` proving the renderer is authenticated.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Typecheck + lint green\n- [x] Automated verification for all plan checkboxes that didn't need external secrets\n- [x] Dev boot end-to-end with real Clerk env; sign-in flow succeeds\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added Sentry integration for improved error tracking and diagnostics in the desktop application.\n\n* **Infrastructure & Build**\n  * Enhanced GitHub Actions workflows for automated desktop CI and releases with source map uploads.\n  * Strengthened environment configuration validation for improved build stability.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->"
    }
